comments: Morant (MEM) goes to the ground to pursue the loose ball and any contact by Russell (MIN) or Vanderbilt (MIN) before they cleanly tie it up is deemed marginal. A jump ball between Vanderbilt and Morant is correctly whistled.
Bane (MEM) makes clean ball contact to temporarily dislodge it from McDaniels (MIN) after he secures the tipped jump ball.
During the drive, Brooks (MEM) places a resting arm to Russell's (MIN) front and marginal contact occurs with his arm as he immediately removes it.
Brooks (MEM) and Towns (MIN) engage and disengage off-ball in the post and the contact is marginal.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Towns (MIN) throws an errant pass across the court and it goes off of McDaniels' (MIN) hands out of bounds.
Tillman (MEM) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Russell (MIN).
Anderson (MEM) is in the paint for around three seconds when the shot is imminent.
McDaniels (MIN) brings his arm down and makes contact with Morant's (MEM) head, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Brooks (MEM) makes contact with Russell (MIN) and it dislodges him out of bounds.
Tillman (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in McDaniels' (MIN) path and absorbs the contact.
Tillman (MEM) legally contests Russell's (MIN) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
During the rebound, Towns (MIN) has his hands resting on Anderson's (MEM) back and marginal contact occurs as he releases for the ball that goes over their heads.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Towns (MIN) throws an errant pass across the court that goes out of bounds.
Vanderbilt (MIN) runs to and through Morant's (MEM) body, which knocks him to the ground.
McDaniels (MIN) commits a take foul on Morant (MEM).
During the inbound, Towns (MIN) cuts to the perimeter and incidental contact occurs with Anderson (MEM) as they briefly come together.
Okogie (MIN) reaches in and makes contact to Bane's (MEM) arm.
